{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775861313691,"sessionID":"ses_2866b12a8ffeIHii9DrS9i1fWL","part":{"id":"prt_d799528c1001nu1hf5redi9Nk2","messageID":"msg_d799518e6001g3WuRf0ZKnGQXH","sessionID":"ses_2866b12a8ffeIHii9DrS9i1fWL","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_0059ed7af0874159a1b4cb89","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-021/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-021/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-021 — CLI build 命令\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the CLI build command in the AgentCube CLI tool (`kubectl-agentcube`).\n6: \n7: ## Base Specifications\n8: \n9: - **AR**: AR-021\n10: - **Module**: `cmd/cli`\n11: - **Language**: Python\n12: - **Size**: M\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## Background\n17: \n18: The `build` command is the second step in the AgentCube workflow. It builds a container image from a packaged workspace using local Docker when `build_mode` is `local` (default in metadata), with optional proxy and tag derived from metadata version.\n19: \n20: ---\n21: \n22: ## Requirements\n23: \n24: ### AR-021-001: CLI interface\n25: \n26: The system SHALL expose the `build` command via Typer with specific options.\n27: \n28: #### Scenario: AR-021-001-A — Build command options\n29: \n30: - **GIVEN** the user runs `kubectl-agentcube build --help`\n31: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL display:\n32:   - `-f, --workspace PATH` — Path to agent workspace (default: \".\")\n33:   - `-p, --proxy URL` — Custom proxy URL for dependency resolution\n34:   - `--cloud-provider NAME` — Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei)\n35:   - `--output PATH` — Output path for build artifacts\n36:   - `--verbose` — Enable detailed logging\n37: \n38: #### Scenario: AR-021-001-B — Default options\n39: \n40: - **GIVEN** the user runs `build` with no options\n41: - **THEN** defaults SHALL be applied:\n42:   - `workspace`: `\".\"`\n43:   - `proxy`: `None`\n44:   - `cloud_provider`: `None`\n45:   - `output`: `None`\n46:   - `verbose`: `False`\n47: \n48: ---\n49: \n50: ### AR-021-002: Build prerequisites validation\n51: \n52: The system SHALL validate build prerequisites before proceeding with the build.\n53: \n54: #### Scenario: AR-021-002-A — Validate workspace exists\n55: \n56: - **GIVEN** the specified workspace path does not exist\n57: - **WHEN** `BuildRuntime._validate_build_prerequisites` runs\n58: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `FileNotFoundError` with message indicating workspace does not exist\n59: \n60: #### Scenario: AR-021-002-B — Validate metadata exists\n61: \n62: - **GIVEN** the workspace does not contain `agent_metadata.yaml`\n63: - **WHEN** `BuildRuntime.build` runs\n64: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `FileNotFoundError` indicating missing metadata file\n65: \n66: #### Scenario: AR-021-002-C — Validate Docker availability for local build\n67: \n68: - **GIVEN** `build_mode` resolves to `\"local\"` in metadata\n69: - **WHEN** Docker is unavailable or not running\n70: - **THEN** `BuildRuntime._validate_build_prerequisites` SHALL raise `RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")`\n71: \n72: ---\n73: \n74: ### AR-021-003: Local Docker build\n75: \n76: The system SHALL build a container image from a packaged workspace using local Docker.\n77: \n78: #### Scenario: AR-021-003-A — Execute local Docker build\n79: \n80: - **GIVEN** local build mode is enabled and Docker is available\n81: - **WHEN** `BuildRuntime._build_local` runs\n82: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n83:   - Use `DockerService.build_image` to build the image\n84:   - Tag the image as `{image_name}:{tag}` where tag is derived from metadata version (default: \"latest\")\n85:   - Return build result with `image_name`, `image_id`, `image_size`, `build_time`\n86: \n87: #### Scenario: AR-021-003-B — Build with custom proxy\n88: \n89: - **GIVEN** `--proxy` option is provided\n90: - **WHEN** `DockerService.build_image` is called\n91: - **THEN** the system SHALL pass proxy settings as build args to Docker\n92: \n93: #### Scenario: AR-021-003-C — Build output path\n94: \n95: - **GIVEN** `--output` option specifies a custom directory\n96: - **WHEN** build completes successfully\n97: - **THEN** the system SHALL store build artifacts in the specified output directory\n98: \n99: #### Scenario: AR-021-003-D — Build failure handling\n100: \n101: - **GIVEN** Docker build fails due to Dockerfile error or missing dependencies\n102: - **WHEN** `BuildRuntime._build_local` raises an exception\n103: - **THEN** the system SHALL propagate the error with meaningful message\n104: - **AND** exit with code `1`\n105: \n106: ---\n107: \n108: ### AR-021-004: Cloud build\n109: \n110: The system SHALL support building container images in the cloud when `build_mode` is `\"cloud\"`.\n111: \n112: #### Scenario: AR-021-004-A — Cloud build execution\n113: \n114: - **GIVEN** `build_mode` resolves to `\"cloud\"` in metadata\n115: - **WHEN** `BuildRuntime._build_cloud` runs\n116: - **THEN** the system SHALL delegate the build to the specified cloud provider\n117: - **AND** return build result with image URL and metadata\n118: \n119: #### Scenario: AR-021-004-B — Cloud provider configuration\n120: \n121: - **GIVEN** `--cloud-provider` option is provided (e.g., \"huawei\")\n122: - **WHEN** cloud build is triggered\n123: - **THEN** the system SHALL use the specified provider's build service\n124: \n125: #### Scenario: AR-021-004-C — Default cloud provider\n126: \n127: - **GIVEN** `build_mode` is `\"cloud\"` but `--cloud-provider` is not specified\n128: - **WHEN** cloud build is triggered\n129: - **THEN** the system SHALL use a default cloud provider or raise `ValueError`\n130: \n131: ---\n132: \n133: ### AR-021-005: Version increment\n134: \n135: The system SHALL increment the metadata version before building.\n136: \n137: #### Scenario: AR-021-005-A — Patch version increment\n138: \n139: - **GIVEN** metadata contains a semantic version (e.g., \"1.2.3\")\n140: - **WHEN** `BuildRuntime._increment_version` runs\n141: - **THEN** the version SHALL be incremented as a patch (e.g., \"1.2.4\")\n142: \n143: #### Scenario: AR-021-005-B — Version increment fallback\n144: \n145: - **GIVEN** metadata version is not in semver format or is `None`\n146: - **WHEN** `_increment_version` runs\n147: - **THEN** the system SHALL append \".1\" to the existing version or use \"0.0.1\" as fallback\n148: \n149: #### Scenario: AR-021-005-C — Version rollback on build failure\n150: \n151: - **GIVEN** build fails after version increment\n152: - **WHEN** exception is caught in `BuildRuntime.build`\n153: - **THEN** the system SHALL revert the version in metadata to the original value\n154: \n155: ---\n156: \n157: ### AR-021-006: Build metadata update\n158: \n159: The system SHALL update the workspace metadata with build results.\n160: \n161: #### Scenario: AR-021-006-A — Update metadata after successful build\n162: \n163: - **GIVEN** build completes successfully\n164: - **WHEN** `BuildRuntime._update_build_metadata` runs\n165: - **THEN** the system SHALL save the updated `AgentMetadata` to `{workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml`\n166: - **AND** include build result fields: `image`, `version`, build timestamp\n167: \n168: #### Scenario: AR-021-006-B — Store image information\n169: \n170: - **GIVEN** build completes successfully\n171: - **WHEN** metadata is updated\n172: - **THEN** the `image` field SHALL be populated with:\n173:   - `image_name`: The full image name with tag\n174:   - `image_id`: Docker image ID\n175:   - `image_size`: Size in bytes\n176:   - `build_time`: ISO timestamp\n177: \n178: ---\n179: \n180: ### AR-021-007: Error handling\n181: \n182: The system SHALL handle errors with appropriate error messages and exit codes.\n183: \n184: #### Scenario: AR-021-007-A — Build error with verbose logging\n185: \n186: - **GIVEN** `BuildRuntime.build` raises an exception\n187: - **WHEN** `--verbose` flag is enabled\n188: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print error message in red with full traceback\n189: - **AND** exit with code `1`\n190: \n191: #### Scenario: AR-021-007-B — Build error without verbose\n192: \n193: - **GIVEN** `BuildRuntime.build` raises an exception\n194: - **WHEN** `--verbose` flag is NOT enabled\n195: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print error message in red without traceback\n196: - **AND** exit with code `1`\n197: \n198: #### Scenario: AR-021-007-C — Handle missing Dockerfile\n199: \n200: - **GIVEN** workspace does not contain a Dockerfile\n201: - **WHEN** local build is attempted\n202: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `FileNotFoundError` indicating Dockerfile is required\n203: \n204: ---\n205: \n206: ### AR-021-008: Successful build output\n207: \n208: The system SHALL display success messages with build details using Rich formatting.\n209: \n210: #### Scenario: AR-021-008-A — Display build success\n211: \n212: - **GIVEN** build completes successfully\n213: - **WHEN** the command finishes\n214: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL display success message with:\n215:   - Image name and tag\n216:   - Image size\n217:   - Build time\n218:   - Using Rich `Progress` spinner during work\n219: \n220: ---\n221: \n222: ## Acceptance Criteria\n223: \n224: - [ ] AC001: Build command accepts all specified CLI options\n225: - [ ] AC002: Build validates workspace and metadata exist before proceeding\n226: - [ ] AC003: Build validates Docker availability for local builds\n227: - [ ] AC004: Local Docker build executes successfully with proper tagging\n228: - [ ] AC005: Build supports proxy configuration for Docker\n229: - [ ] AC006: Cloud build delegates to specified provider\n230: - [ ] AC007: Version is incremented before build\n231: - [ ] AC008: Version is reverted on build failure\n232: - [ ] AC009: Build metadata is updated with image information\n233: - [ ] AC010: Build displays success output with Rich formatting\n234: - [ ] AC011: Build handles errors with appropriate exit codes and verbose logging\n235: \n236: ---\n237: \n238: ## Architecture Notes\n239: \n240: ### Key Components\n241: \n242: | Component | Path | Description |\n243: |-----------|------|-------------|\n244: | CLI Entry | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Typer app with `build` command |\n245: | BuildRuntime | `agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py` | Core build logic |\n246: | DockerService | `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | Docker SDK operations |\n247: | MetadataService | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | Metadata CRUD operations |\n248: | AgentMetadata | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | Pydantic model for agent config |\n249: \n250: ### Build Flow\n251: \n252: ```\n253: build command\n254:     └─> BuildRuntime.build()\n255:             ├─> _validate_build_prerequisites()\n256:             ├─> _increment_version()\n257:             ├─> _build_local() or _build_cloud()\n258:             │       └─> DockerService.build_image()\n259:             └─> _update_build_metadata()\n260: ```\n261: \n262: ### CLI Options Mapping\n263: \n264: | CLI Option | Runtime Parameter | Type |\n265: |------------|-------------------|------|\n266: | `-f, --workspace` | workspace_path | str |\n267: | `-p, --proxy` | options[\"proxy\"] | Optional[str] |\n268: | `--cloud-provider` | options[\"cloud_provider\"] | Optional[str] |\n269: | `--output` | options[\"output\"] | Optional[str] |\n270: | `--verbose` | verbose | bool |\n271: \n272: ---\n273: \n274: ## References\n275: \n276: - Base design: `cli-toolkit/design.md`\n277: - Base spec: `cli-toolkit/spec.md`\n278: - CLI entry point: `agentcube/cli/main.py`\n279: - Runtime implementation: `agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py`\n280: - Docker service: `agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n281: - Metadata model: `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n\n(End of file - total 281 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-021 — CLI build 命令\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the CLI build command in the AgentCube CLI tool (`kubectl-agentcube`).\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-021\n- **Module**: `cmd/cli`\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: M\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nThe `build` command is the second step in the AgentCube workflow. It builds a container image from a packaged workspace using local Docker when `build_mode` is `local` (default in metadata), with optional proxy and tag derived from metadata version.\n\n---","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-021/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775861313676,"end":1775861313690}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775861313694,"sessionID":"ses_2866b12a8ffeIHii9DrS9i1fWL","part":{"id":"prt_d79952cbd001cKSFtI472ejcFD","messageID":"msg_d799518e6001g3WuRf0ZKnGQXH","sessionID":"ses_2866b12a8ffeIHii9DrS9i1fWL","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_d29c161f32a74cbbafceec15","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-021/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-021/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-021 — CLI build 命令 Tasks\n2: \n3: **Module:** cmd/cli  \n4: **Language:** Python  \n5: **Size:** M  \n6: **Stage:** ST-1 (Concept)\n7: \n8: ---\n9: \n10: ## Phase 1: Project Setup\n11: \n12: - [ ] **T001** (placeholder)\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## Dependencies\n17: \n18: **To be determined after spec is finalized.**\n19: \n20: ---\n21: \n22: ## Verification Commands\n23: \n24: ```bash\n25: # Run build command\n26: kubectl-agentcube build --help\n27: \n28: # Run tests\n29: pytest tests/ -v\n30: ```\n31: \n32: ---\n33: \n34: ## Notes\n35: \n36: - Design stage ST-1 - concept phase, spec to be defined\n37: - Depends on AR-020 (pack command) being complete\n\n(End of file - total 37 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-021 — CLI build 命令 Tasks\n\n**Module:** cmd/cli  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M  \n**Stage:** ST-1 (Concept)\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1: Project Setup\n\n- [ ] **T001** (placeholder)\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n**To be determined after spec is finalized.**\n\n---","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-021/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775861313682,"end":1775861313692}}}}
